Rating: 4
First made and reviewed this excellent soup in Jan/02 and have made it numerous times since then and it has always been a hit. Made it again yesterday but, after reading each review, I made a few changes that made this already great recipe even better. 1) Added 4 large cloves of minced garlic to the veggie mix instead of my usual 2 cloves. 2) Added 1 cup of very small sea shell pasta following the addition of broth and before adding the cream rather than cooking it separately. Perfect pasta for this soup! 3)Used boneless/skinless chicken breasts which I browned/sauteed in a little butter and sprinkled with salt, pepper, onion powder and garlic powder; removed from pan and diced; deglazed the pan with 1/2 cup chicken broth; added the diced chicken back to the pan for a few minutes to reheat before adding to the soup near the end of cooking. This added a deeper depth of flavour to the finished soup and the chicken was more tender. 4) Maintained my usual juice and finely grated zest of 1 lemon added to the soup a few minutes before serving. The lemon zest imparts so much flavour without making the soup too tangy/acidic. It is the lemon that distinguishes this soup from every other chicken soup and elevates it far beyond the ordinary. Otherwise, I followed the recipe. This is a great soup as written, but with these changes it is nothing short of sublime! Don't understand how anyone could find this soup bland and boring. This is down-home comfort food with a surprising, gourmet twist! Enjoy!

