This recipe was wonderful. Made the soup the day before excepted for adding the penne and sugarsnap peas. Did cook the penne the day before and used the mini penne and stored in refrg in plastic bag. Added 1/2 tsp of dried tarragon and used a little more chicken. I did saute the chicken first, removed, cooked veggies and then continued with the recipe. Used it for a group of friends on our game night and they loved it. Served in a cup and also served a big tossed salad, crusty bread and dessert. it served 10 people approximately 1 1/4 C servings each. Will make this again soon. The sugarsnap peas and the lemon juice really add a lot to the recipe. Was concerned that it was not thick, but it was perfect. May try fatfree half and half next time to cut back on calories and could reduce the butter by a T or so.

