This is a very good variation of my standard chicken stock/soup recipe and a nice change to the ordinary. I make my own chicken stock and cook the vegetables in it, then when it's done I chop them and return them to the strained broth, and then just add the lemon juice, cream (I used whipping cream and a lesser amount) fresh chopped parsley and cut up pieces of chicken from the fryer used to make the stock. I also added a can of diced tomatoes which added beautiful color to the mix of the other vegetables. Next time I think I will add some spinach. Also used garlic to make the stock. This soup is even better the next day after the flavors have time to blend.

